inn1.comm: moving across the left-hander first up from a length outside leg, pushed towards extra cover and they are away with a single
straight and very wide down leg
ending on leg stump after pitching outside it, tucked easily towards square leg
much better line from PK, finishing around middle and off on a good length, tapped towards point
decent start from PK apart from that wide, around middle again on a tight length, pushed away on the off side
opens up as he sees the line is on leg, tries to work it away square, but it hits the outer side of the blade and rolls down the track
angled far across the left-hander who lets it go
back of a length and cramping him for room with the angle, pushed away

pitched up now, but tight line just outside off and defended hurriedly, the ball has now dribbled away towards deep midwicket and they trot across for two overthrows, which are ultimately disallowed as the ball was deemed dead by then, despite neither the bowler nor the keeper getting a hand to it
pushed on the off side, the line is just around off, and the angle is into the left-hander, tucking him up
this time he waits a shade and nudges it towards square leg with the angle
left alone outside off
nippy length delivery that bounces a tad, he cannot work it away square
Warner gets some width and flashes at it, sending it scurrying past extra cover, long boundaries here, and it is eventually pulled back after what seems an eternity
well done, drops it in front of square leg and sets off, a clean pick-up from the man running in might have made it close
good delivery, just outside off stump on a length, Warner hangs his bat inside the line and is beaten
this one nipped back in sharply from outside off, Warner was pushing forward and takes it high on the thigh pad off an inside edge
back and across as he looks to work on the leg side but ends up nudging to midwicket
left alone outside off
136.4 kph from Vinay just outside off, Wade is surprised as it nips and bounces across him, jabs it away to third man
tucked up with the incoming angle, pushed away from the crease
thick edge this time as he pushes hard from the crease, the back of a length ball flies to third man
tight line this, right on middle, defended back to the bowler
stays in the crease, and drops the length delivery on the off side from close to the body, they are through with the run by the time point reaches the ball
he hasn't been allowed room at all so far, this time he has a swing as he sees this rare widish delivery outside off, misses
too good for Wade, angled in on a good length, he comes forward to drive, it straightens after pitching and beats him totally
pushed away on the off side
shot! this will reach the boundary even on this huge outfield, pitched up a tad fuller, he gets a bit of width to comes forward and go through with the big drive, and it races to the extra cover rope
defends an incoming delivery
smashed off the front foot, he went after that one, but hit it straight to extra cover
good length on middle, defended down the track

he's bowled Warner! they have not allowed him an inch of room, apart from one wide delivery, this one was pitched up from around the wicket, coming in on the stumps, Warner lunged at it and had a big heave, missed, and the ball rattled the middle stump, Vinay is pumped up, some relief for him after he was taken apart by Warner in Perth
shaping away at 134.7 kph some way outside off, Ponting lets it go
moves a long way across outside off and shoulders arms to a good length ball that bounces nicely through to Dhoni
superb line this, at 138.1 kph, Ponting slightly uncertain whether to play at this pitched up delivery close to off, and allows it to go in the end
lots of bounce from just short of a length, he comes forward, drops it close to the pitch on the off side and gets off the mark
this is probing stuff from Vinay, ending very close to off stump from over the stumps, Wade runs it to point
hangs in the air on a good length and comes back in sharply, but starts too far outside off and is left alone comfortably
sends it full on the pads, and Ponting flicks eagerly down to fine leg
excellent line, shaping across Wade from leg stump, he stays in the crease and pokes at it, beaten
hangs back and opens the face to run this one down to third man as it moves across him from back of a length
pushed back to the bowler
moving away a tad outside off, pushed towards cover
Vinay is getting good bounce and nip, Wade stays back and runs this one to third man
hits high on the bat as he comes forward to a short of a length ball

it is overcast and Vinay and PK are testing Australia, this is not the Vinay who turned up in Perth, Ponting lunges forward as he sees it pitching on a length, but it rears up and moves away a bit to beat him
pushed off the front foot to mid off

he's got Ponting now, Vinay has bowled much better deliveries than this one today, Ponting saw some rare width and went to punch it, it seemed to sit up a tad from short of a length and he ended up hitting it straight to short extra cover
136.5 kph, bounce, bit of away shape from a good length, Clarke lets it go immediately
runs it to third man for a single
moves forward and nudges the length ball to short midwicket
worked off the pad but there is square leg in place
this time Clarke gets it past midwicket with a work off leg stump

huge appeal for leg-before, looked like an inside edge, else he was gone, yes, replays show a big inside edge, the ball came in quickly from a good length, and Clarke pushed well in front away from the body
nudged behind square leg
it is not the pace, it is fine but not threatening, but the bounce that Vinay is getting which is troubling Australia, Clarke is hit on the thigh pad now
pitched up, and he gets forward to push hard to extra cover
similar to the one that Ponting mishit to short extra cover, Clarke pats it away towards mid off
pitched up on the stumps, he motions forward and eases it to mid on
can't get it away, good length on middle, he opens up a tad but pushes it to mid on again
not completely in control but gets the drive past a diving extra cover
fullish, shaping away a bit, ending around middle, pushed from the crease
no room at all, length ball on middle and leg, pushed down the track
towards leg this time, but he has no pace to work it past midwicket
comes forward and opens the face to push a fullish one to covers
whoa, that came out of nowhere, that is huge, Wade has had enough of this nagging line from PK, he puts front foot out and clobbers a length ball high over deep midwicket
width, Wade cashes in, goes hard at the cut, and it flies over point for another boundary
gentle wide delivery, would have been called one had Clarke not reached out to pat it away
length ball pushed down the track, Virat dives to his right and stops it
eased down to long on for one
way down the leg side to the left-hander, Dhoni does well to get a glove to it
angled across Wade who pushes to extra cover
pushed off the back foot to midwicket
no pace to work with, even though he gets some width, he cannot time the shot as he looks to hammer it, gets it wide of extra cover in the end
fired in fullish on to the pads, worked in front of square
too short from around the stumps, Wade makes room and bashes it straight to extra cover
better delivery, pitched up around off, he comes forward and pushes to covers for one
shortish delivery, Clarke swings it away behind square leg off the front foot
pushed hard off the back foot to long off
looks to guide a flat and straight one fine past the keeper but misses
pushes a tossed up ball back to Ashwin, in the air for a while
turns across him from leg stump, he backs away and cuts wide of sweeper cover for a well-run two
pushes back a length ball to Ashwin
cramped for room with the straight delivery on middle and leg, punches it to the left of Ashwin who does well to dive and stop the single
nudged to fine leg off the pad
another straight delivery from a length, Clarke stays back and hits it back to the bowler
again Wade drives hard and finds extra cover
shortish and spinning across, he makes room and gets it to sweeper cover
Clarke takes on the flighted ball from around the stumps and lofts it straight to deep midwicket, part-timer picks up a crucial wicket
pushes a flighted ball to extra cover
guides a flat delivery to sweeper cover
tight line on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
flighted offbreak spins away outside off, he stays in the crease and cuts behind point
worked towards midwicket and Hussey charges across for the run
bounce for Ashwin from a length, but Wade plays the cut superbly past cover, stopped just inside the rope
ending on middle from a good length, he moves well across and nudges behind square leg
misfield, cut shot goes through Virat at point as he winces in pain
tries to cut this one but it bounces too much and beats him
Wade charges down the track, Rohit drags it short, Wade flails and an inside edge past Dhoni saves him
he got hold of this one alright, short again, on middle, he backs away, opens up and thumps it over midwicket
much fuller on leg, pushed in front of square leg
not short enough but Hussey has time to pull it through midwicket
Hussey gets another one away, the line is on leg and he is down on a knee in a flash to sweep it to the deep square leg boundary
straightish delivery, he pushes it on the leg side with a bit of an inside edge
sweeper cover is working overtime, Wade chops another cut wide of him
moves across to a flighted ball and works it to fine leg
fired flat and wide across the left-hander, the cut is mistimed but worth a single still, Rohit's throw is wayward and allows one more
smack! Wade sees this one pitch on leg and instantly bends the knee to slog-sweep it to the deep midwicket boundary
that kept low, and Wade under-edged the attempted cut onto Dhoni's pads
sharp, quick one fired in on middle and leg, he gets a lot of bounce and gets a leading edge on the off side
and this full delivery grazes the outside edge and goes between Dhoni and the wide slip
flat delivery cut through point for a couple
beats him outside off with a quick one that goes across with the angle
worked towards vacant midwicket, Dhoni immediately goes 'bhaag jaa (run), Rahul' as the bowler bounds after it awkwardly, the fielder comes in from the deep to keep them to one, Wade has to dive back
cannot get the cut past point
swept fine on the leg side
too wide and too short, he reaches out to slap it away, and they scamper back for the second
short-arm jabs a length ball through midwicket
jabs away this one on the leg side, that single takes Wade to 50, I don't see Haddin playing any time soon for Australia in limited-overs at least
Hussey latches onto the sweep, from outside off stump, and times it superbly behind square leg, no chance for fine leg
shot! this is smart hitting from Hussey, he is picking the gaps all the time, short-arm pulls a quickish length ball through midwicket now
full delivery driven neatly off the front foot to long off
busy again from Hussey, pushes softly in front of extra cover and another run is taken easily
lets a widish one go outside off
beaten as he looks to make room for the cut, but the bounce is too much
moves across and taps on the leg side for one
lots of width, the cut is on, and hard running gives them two more, this is a fantastic partnership, just what Australia needed on resumption
shortish one slapped away to extra cover
incredible running, the throw was loopy from deep midwicket, and they make the second comfortably in the end
clatter! Wade fetches a full one from outside off and hammers it over wide long on
punches past point and another couple of runs are taken, nowhere to hide in the field
slapped to sweeper cover for one
whipped from outside off to deep midwicket
worked off the front foot through midwicket
driven to wide long off for one and an overthrow gives them another
smashes the cut hard through point, sweeper cover has to get to his right really fast
96.9 kph and angled across outside off, beats him on the cut
pushes a full delivery back to the bowler

inside-edged on to the stumps, Wade was getting beaten on the cut by the quick deliveries, he looked to open up and pull this time, the ball was not short enough, and he plays on, fantastic innings on ODI debut though
worked behind square leg
thick outside edge past slip as he pushes forward, Rahul dives but cannot stop it cleanly
worked with the spin through square leg
pushed off the front foot to extra cover
coming in with the angle, pushed past extra cover, Jadeja has overstepped
low full toss, Michael Hussey is not going to miss out, bends the knee and lifts it over midwicket
worked to deep midwicket
remains in the crease and cuts a length ball to point
runs the full delivery with an open face behind point, and the brothers are through immediately for the run
pushed  back to the bowler
drives an angled delivery to long off
just past the off stump, oh, was that close, flat and quick delivery, slightly short, and he shaped up to pull, but was beaten as it straightened with pace
worked square on the leg side, the throw would have tested them on the second, but instead a ricochet gets them the third
short, sitting up, and hammered over deep midwicket, need no invitation when it is that short
tries the carrom ball, short again, David Hussey opens up and pulls again, gets two less than the previous stroke for his effort
third short ball on the trot, this time he will get only one through midwicket
appeal for lbw as he is struck in front of leg stump, but that pitched outside leg
guided behind point from the crease
this is furious high-quality running, worked through midwicket and they hare back for the second
not the best delivery he has bowled today, way too short outside off, but Michael Hussey has shovelled the pull straight to deep square leg, he's given the run-rate a serious boost though
guides a length delivery very late down to third man
drops this one on the off side for his first run in ODIs
clatter! overpitched, wide, David Hussey gets front leg out of the way and smashes it through extra cover
well done, waits for this one to arrive on off and runs it behind point
pitched up on off, he defends it back to Vinay
makes room and punches through point from off stump
pushes a full delivery down to long on
quick and not that short, he opens up to pull it down to long on
guided towards point for a single
fired down the leg side, he misses the sweep, Dhoni misses the take
worked for a couple to deep midwicket
smartly done, worked softly through vacant midwicket for two more
misses the pull to a short of a length ball as it bounces more than he expected outside off, almost head high
well fielded, leaps in the air to stop Christian's push to a very full delivery
moves across and swings this one from middle, goes on the bounce to short fine leg
charges down the track and slogs a length ball to long on
goes hard at a pitched up delivery and slices it over cover
makes room as Vinay keeps it full outside off, slaps it away through point
sweeps from leg stump to fine leg
looks to slog-sweep over midwicket, but the inside edge races away towards the fine leg boundary, only to be stopped by Vinay with a big slide as he parries the ball to the chasing fielder
down the track and blasts it straight at the umpire, who gets out of the way just in time
dabbed away on the off side for a single
makes room even as he keeps it full on middle and leg, inside edge behind square leg results from a big swing
guided through point for one
low full toss way down the leg side and he helps it past short fine
similar delivery, not as much down leg as the previous one, and he is hit on the boot as he misses
slower length ball now, he adjusts his swing to work it towards square leg

dropped, good attempt by Rohit at deep midwicket, it was a leading edge off a low full toss, it looped in the air and Rohit grabbed it with both hands as he put in the dive, but it popped out as he hit the ground
swung to fine leg, who has gone back to the boundary
steps out but hits the full delivery back to Rahul
down the track again and works to deep midwicket for a couple
full delivery smacked to midwicket, the throw is from an off-balance Tendulkar, and allows them to complete the single
fifty for David Hussey as he backs away outside leg, Jadeja fires it in on a length, and he mows it over deep midwicket
pushed to covers for one
fired in wide outside off, and called one
and he bowls a no-ball now, fires it on on leg stump, worked behind square leg
low full toss and David Hussey finishes off on a high, clattering it way over deep midwicket

inn2.comm: right on middle on a good length, pushed on the leg side but Harris gets to it quickly
bouncing delivery but down the leg side
beaten outside off as he pushes at one going across him
back of a length ball dropped to cover from the crease
carved over extra cover, Gautam makes room and slices the pitched up delivery over the in-field
pushed off the front foot towards extra cover
hurried into a defensive push to a straightening length ball
Starc starts off at 141 kph from a length, worked behind square leg
goes across to an angled length ball and pushes back to the bowler
swings in sharply but starts on leg and carries down the leg side
straightening on middle and leg, nudged to square leg
144.8 kph delivery angled too far wide across the right hander
bit of width and he guides it wide of third man for a couple

he's gone! Ponting takes out Tendulkar, Starc pitches it up wide, not full enough, Tendulkar reaches out and goes for the drive, it flies low to Ponting's right, and the veteran goes down to take it safely, he is mobbed by his team-mates
146 kph length delivery left alone as it angles across outside off
bowls it wide down the leg side
left alone quietly as it shapes across him
shot! Gautam leans into the drive but a superb diving stop from Warner at cover saves a few runs
checks his forward push on the off side as this one bounces from a good length
stays back and gets across to defend a pitched up ball
lovely delivery, holding its line as it is bowled fullish outside off, Virat goes pushing at it and is beaten
opens the face and runs this back of a length ball to third man
goes reaching out to a wide pitched up delivery, similar to the one that got Sachin, Virat is beaten though, as he did not move his feet well enough
outside edge and gone! super stuff from Starc, Gautam falls to a nick outside off again, Starc gets it to rear up at him from back of a length, and Gautam pokes it on its way to the keeper
almost another one, Rohit gets a wide and short one, and has a waft at it to get beaten
coming in from a length an bounces to strike Rohit on the thigh pad
reaches out to a short and wide one again, and it goes in the air towards third man, couple of bounces before he gets to it
solid push from Virat, the pitched up delivery races to mid off
he tends to come forward more often than not, and this time is beaten as he pushes at one holding its line
this time he stays in the crease, and drops the shortish one behind point for a quick single, throw misses at the striker's end
almost got him, just short of a diving shortish mid on as Rohit pushes loosely off the front foot
this time he plays tightly towards mid on
opens the face and squeezes the full delivery between cover and point
beaten outside off as he has flails at a bouncing short of a length ball going across him
goes for the pull, not timed well, but he will get three for his effort
eases a pitched up ball back to the bowler
slashes at a widish one, and it flies down to third man
gets forward and pushes a length delivery back to Starc
too good, draws him forward with the fuller length, and beats him with the angle
inside edge races past the stumps to fine leg as he goes for the cover drive, it nipped in a tad after pitching on a fuller length
shot! full marks for intent to Virat as he lunges forward and smacks this pitched up delivery over extra cover
drops the length ball in front of cover from the crease and they hare across for the run
and now Rohit, eases on to the front foot and swings the full delivery high over extra cover, one bounce for four
superb comeback from Harris, Rohit was looking to launch into another big stroke, but the length was shorter this time, so he checked the shot, but it also held its line to beat him completely
swing and a miss to end the over as Rohit fails in his attempt to slog over midwicket
lovely stroke from Virat, he steps out and makes room to power this one over extra cover
moves across and pushes an angled length ball on the off side
gets across again and works from off in front of square leg, and will come back for the second, well done
Starc gets low and gets a hand to this drive in his followthrough, the ball is struck firmly enough to ricochet as far as mid on
pushed to mid off for a single
another inside edge to fine leg, Rohit pushing in slow motion with an angled blade
worked with the angle off the pad towards midwicket
the bouncer get big on Virat, but he swivels and goes hard at the pull, gets it in the air but over midwicket and into the boundary
leading edge flies past point wide of third man as he looks to work from outside off to leg
hangs his bat at a widish length delivery and belatedly withdraws the bat
and again, Harris is getting it to straighten after angling it in widish outside off, Virat goes reaching out again and misses
chopped down to third man from close to the body
advances down the track and makes room, eyeing the extra cover boundary again, but mishits it to mid off this time
pushed softly in front of point for one
Rohit is looking very loose out there, pushes away from the body to one angled across, and is beaten
third inside edge for Rohit as he pushes with an angled bat, the ball goes in front of square leg
outside edge flies past a diving slip for four, Rohit sees it pitched up very wide and goes after it
145.7 kph high full toss close to off, he does well to open the face and guide it to third man
loopy wide delivery first up, flashed hard on the bounce to third man
shot! Virat is turning it on with some crisp strokes, drives hard in the ground, and it bounces over extra cover to race to the boundary
opens the face to a short of a length ball and runs it to third man
very awkward looking half-pull falls just short of midwicket as Rohit plays the stroke on one leg
worked behind square leg off the pads
on the pads and worked behind square leg for a couple of runs
Ponting at shortish backward point holds on to the screamer, Virat was batting superbly but he is gone now, cuts a wide delivery hard but straight to Ponting
runs it to third man with an open face

McKay strikes again, India deep in trouble now, short of a length and getting big on Rohit, who has looked like getting out any moment, moves away just a bit after pitching and Rohit can only fend it to the keeper
moves across to a back of a length ball and works it through square leg
moves forward and eases the pitched up ball to sweeper cover
pushed away on the off side
pops up off a leading edge down the wicket as he looks to work on the leg side
jabs a full delivery away to point
short ball and he checks the pull to fine leg
late in getting bat down to one headed for the stumps, jabs it on the leg side in the end
targetting the stumps again with a pitched up ball, Dhoni works it late behind square leg
whoa, that has been clobbered between extra cover and mid off, pitched up delivery, he stays in the crease and powers it into the gap, all hands
gets across and defends a length ball
he is in the air as he smashes another pitched up ball from the crease, this time to sweeper cover
worked off the pads to fine leg
moves a long way across, and the ball pops up off the thigh pad on the leg side, they go through with the run
appeal for leg before but that one pitched outside leg
flashed away hard to the man at sweeper cover, he is going for his shots

oh dear, Raina has fallen to the short ball, to Dan Christian, not the most threatening bowler going around, goes for an awkward pull, off the front foot, and only ends up lobbing the ball for midwicket to take a dolly running to his right
leaves alone a sharply rising back of a length ball outside off
length ball whipped through midwicket for one
gets across and carefully pats away a length ball on the off side
opens up and pushed through extra cover for a single
comes down the track and pushes to the bowler's right for a single, Doherty rushes quickly and slides to stop the ball
worked through square leg with the spin
extra cover cannot stop the ball and they take the single to long off
short and flat, slapped away to sweeper cover
forced from outside off through midwicket
punched back to the bowler
leaves alone one hanging around outside the off stump on a good length
comes in with the angle, nudged to midwicket
pushed off the front foot in front of point for one
rides the bounce on a short of a length ball, it drops close to the pitch off the bat handle
moves well across and works in front of square leg
walks out and nudges off the pads in front of square leg for a comfortable two
shortish one cut hard wide of sweeper cover
spinning in from outside off, pushed back to the bowler
lunges forward and nudges with the spin behind square leg
dabs a widish one but straight to point
beaten on the drive outside off with one that angles past the outside edge
stays in the crease and pushes past extra cover for one
standing open after moving across but cannot push the length ball past the bowler
stays in the crease and swings a pitched up ball down to long off
widish one flashed down to third man for one
legs wide apart, as he whips forcefully through midwicket
pushed off the front foot on the leg side
makes room and cuts for a couple through point
dabs it late fine past the keeper on the off side
driven along the ground to long off
stays back and works on the leg side, Doherty rushes to the ball and throws at the non-striker's but Dhoni is through
forced with the spin down to long on
pitched up delivery driven to mid off
backs away but ends up chopping a widish one
worked off the pads behind square leg and Jadeja comes back for the second
looks to make room and pull a shortish one but withdraws in the end
slower one dragged from outside off down to long on
played out to point from the crease
drives a full delivery to long off
tries to hammer this one out of sight but mistimes it back to the bowler
misses as he swings at a pitched up ball outside off
low full toss swung down to long on
hurled in full and fast very wide outside off, and is called one, marginal call
gets it right this time as he fires it in full and quick closer to the stumps, Dhoni can only slam it back down the track
charges down the track but ends up mishitting the length ball on the off side
well bowled, Dhoni was making room but McKay forced him to check his stroke with a slower one

another one goes! this would have been a six at most grounds in India, McKay banging it in short, Jadeja looks to pull it into the stands beyond deep midwicket but only gets it as far as the man in the deep who holds on as he tumbles to the ground
back of a length ball pops up off an inside edge but there is no one around square leg to take it
short ball awkwardly helped fine on the leg side, Starc runs across and parries it back in as he jumps over the rope
dabbed down to third man, was in the air for some time

superb work in the deep from Christian, Ashwin hung his bat out to a wide and low full toss and got it through point, Christian chased and stopped it with a slide, looked back to see them attempting a third, and steadied himself before aiming at Ashwin's end, knowing that the slower man would struggle to make it, he is caught short by a mile, and more
swung down to long on
backs away and mistimes a slog in front of square leg
even Dhoni would have struggled had the throw from extra cover hit, it didn't
they keep falling, Rahul departs to a full toss, he makes room, and has a big swing at it, only to miss, and the ball crashes into middle
pushes a low full toss towards mid off and they go through for the single
pushed away on the off side
looks to clobber a flighted ball out of sight, but is beaten by the turn
patted back to the bowler
eases a pitched up ball down to long off
smacked straight back at Clarke and it goes through him
whipped through midwicket for a couple
forced to extra cover

Dhoni has holed out to long off, he has been swinging full deliveries hard from the crease, he got hold of this one alright, it flew off the middle high towards Warner, who timed his leap superbly to hold on to it
pushed down the track off the front foot
leading edge pops up and falls in front of point
struck high on the pad with a quicker one, they appeal but the umpire is unmoved
pushed down to long off
hit on the pad as he misses the pull off a short ball, was going down leg
pushed towards cover for a single
patted back to the bowler off the back foot
fine effort from Warner, he scrambles to his right at long on and goes one handed to try and catch a slog from PK, but cannot get to it
worked towards square leg
worked to deep midwicket
down the track and pushes at a flat delivery
pushed to extra cover
makes room and slices over extra cover
pushed to point who has a go at the non-striker's end but misses, direct hit, and it was over
defended off the front foot
flat-batted straight past the bowler, and even Warner cannot stop it this time
whoa, that is an excellent stroke, that has been dismissed, Starc targetting the stumps from around the stumps, but Vinay took on the pitched up delivery and smoked it between extra cover and mid off
dabs a widish one down to third man
rides the bounce from back of a length and takes the single as the ball rolls towards point
beaten on the forward push by the length ball angled across
makes room and squeezes it from around leg stump to third man
dropped, well that spoils what could have been a perfect day for Australia, PK indulges in a upper cut that loops to Harris at third man, he gets around to it, and puts it down
throws his bat at a widish back of a length delivery, cannot get to it
makes room to a slower one and dabs it to extra cover
another slower one, stays low too, he backs away and at the same time looks to pull it, too much to do off one delivery, beaten
Harris redeems himself for dropping a simple catch by taking a brilliant low take, running a long way in from long on, and tumbling forward to hold on to PK's slog
